<paragraph id="039A62C13265310807708830FEA3CE51" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">
<emphasis id="26B5D3FA15ED10231FAA7478D56D8228" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="255">Female.</emphasis>
As in male except as noted. Habitus as in 
<figureCitation id="2F27402EAD46323AD706FEF0D7BC815A" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Opopaea berlandi, female. A, C, E habitus, dorsal, lateral and ventral views B, D, F, G prosoma, dorsal, lateral, ventral and anterior views H abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.4 mm (A, C, E); 0.2 mm (B, D, F-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350627" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" tableDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure3">Fig. 3A, C, E</figureCitation>
. Body length 1.42. Endites without projections. Copulatory organ (
<figureCitation id="DFA79DA02EF87A312A310257D69A33A1" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Opopaea berlandi, female. A, C, E habitus, dorsal, lateral and ventral views B, D, F, G prosoma, dorsal, lateral, ventral and anterior views H abdomen, ventral view. Scale bars: 0.4 mm (A, C, E); 0.2 mm (B, D, F-H)." figureDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350627" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" tableDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure3">Figs 3H</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2BA38EB1624BDF8889532B822CD3A60B" captionStart="Figure 23" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figure 23. Female copulatory organ. A, B Opopaea berlandi C, D Opopaea kulczynskii E, F Opopaea sheldrick sp. nov. A, C, E ventral view B, D, F dorsal view. Abbreviations: apo = apodeme; asr = anterior scutal ridge; ga = globular appendix; lpr = linguiform projection; nlp = nail-like process; pd = postgynal depression; pls = paddle-like sclerite; rds = ring-shaped dark spot; sds = stick-shaped dark spot. Scale bars: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure23" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/350649" pageId="0" pageNumber="255" tableDoi="10.3897/AfrInvertebr.60.39146.figure23">23A, B</figureCitation>
): in the middle of the epigastric scutal ridge there is a dark, linguiform projection; postgynal depression extremely narrow; there is a paddle-like sclerite (pls) dorsally, with thin, smoothly curved arms; nail-like process (nlp) well separated.
</paragraph>
